## Multiple Columns

Set `numColumns` to display items in a grid. When using `numColumns`, `renderItem` receives the item as usual, but the items are arranged in columns.

```jsx
<FlatList
  data={DATA}
  keyExtractor={(item) => item.id}
  numColumns={2}
  renderItem={({ item }) => (
    <View style={{ flex: 1, margin: 5, backgroundColor: 'lightblue' }}>
      <Text>{item.name}</Text>
    </View>
  )}
/>
```

⚠️ You must ensure each item's container has `flex: 1` or a fixed width to share the space evenly.

When all items have the same height, `getItemLayout` eliminates the need to measure them, greatly improving performance.

```jsx
const ITEM_HEIGHT = 50;

<FlatList
  data={DATA}
  keyExtractor={(item) => item.id}
  renderItem={({ item }) => <Text style={{ height: ITEM_HEIGHT }}>{item.title}</Text>}
  getItemLayout={(data, index) => ({
    length: ITEM_HEIGHT,
    offset: ITEM_HEIGHT * index,
    index,
  })}
/>
```
